"{\"uid\": \"townhall.com-columnists-dennisprager-2024-07-30-you-dont-have-to-be-christian-to-loathe-the-opening-of-the-paris-olympics-n2642702\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"I am a Jew, not a Christian.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 28, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9995788376898467, \"rank\": 0.00042133976262630907, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Jew\", \"from\": 5, \"to\": 10}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet I found loathsome the mockery of the Last Supper -- one of the holiest scenes in the New Testament -- during the opening of the 2024 Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 29, \"to\": 184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 178, \"end\": 183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999626757023, \"rank\": 3.732426825898575e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the mockery\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 62}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 66, \"to\": 81}, {\"ngram\": \"the holiest scenes\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 110}, {\"ngram\": \"the New Testament\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 131}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 157, \"to\": 174}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, it is actually troubling to constantly read the words, \\\"Many Christians are offended\\\" -- as if only Christians are offended by France's and the International Olympic Committee's mockery of Jesus' Last Supper scene.\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 256, \"end\": 266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9931681414043927, \"rank\": 0.006101472430751102, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 295, \"end\": 305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9931681414043927, \"rank\": 0.006101472430751102, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 322, \"end\": 328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7348343851884511, \"rank\": 0.3581038710623919, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 339, \"end\": 370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 384, \"end\": 389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999994808128105, \"rank\": 5.191662615086304e-07, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 193}, {\"ngram\": \"the words\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, if only Christians were offended, there is little hope for civilization.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 427, \"end\": 437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9931681414043927, \"rank\": 0.006101472430751102, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"little hope\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"civilization\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we live in the age of groupthink, in which only members of targeted groups are expected to be offended.\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 600, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"groupthink\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 529}, {\"ngram\": \"only members\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 552}, {\"ngram\": \"targeted groups\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To write that Christians were offended by what just transpired in Paris would be as if one were to write, \\\"blacks were offended\\\" by slavery, or \\\"Jews are offended\\\" by Islamic attempts to eradicate Israel; or \\\"women are offended\\\" by the rape of women.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9931681414043927, \"rank\": 0.006101472430751102, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999626757023, \"rank\": 3.732426825898575e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 746, \"end\": 750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.7414400397130523, \"rank\": 0.3487267106945382, \"text\": \"Jews\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}, {\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9963419066991522, \"rank\": 0.002383723123910827, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"blacks\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 714}, {\"ngram\": \"slavery\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 740}, {\"ngram\": \"Islamic attempts\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"the rape\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One assumes that moral individuals of every group would find men in drag, transwomen and a naked man enacting Leonardo da Vinci's painting of the Last Supper -- on the world's largest stage -- offensive.\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 963, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.730939705080609e-19, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"moral individuals\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"every group\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 902}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 917}, {\"ngram\": \"drag\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"transwomen\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 937}, {\"ngram\": \"a naked man\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's largest stage\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1042}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, \\\"offensive\\\" does not do justice to how we all should view what the French and the Olympics did.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9910825541788201, \"rank\": 0.008218242906611552, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"justice\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What was done in the opening to the 2024 Paris Olympics was far more serious than \\\"offensive.\\\"\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1192}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It actually represented the greatest threat to Western civilization in the Western world's history: the Left.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9404912306802652, \"rank\": 0.06327412912748583, \"text\": \"Western civilization\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}, {\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9978959485648325, \"rank\": 0.0021083656377274044, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the greatest threat\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"the Left\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You do not have to be a Christian to understand that Christianity -- more specifically, Judeo-Christian values and the Bible -- made Western civilization.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9995788376898467, \"rank\": 0.00042133976262630907, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999145529755902, \"rank\": 8.545389296436431e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judeo-Christian_ethics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Judeo-Christian values\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judeo-Christian_ethics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judeo-Christian_ethics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Bible\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"Western civilization\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without Christianity and the Bible, there would be no West.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Christianity\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bible\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1559}, {\"ngram\": \"no West\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1583}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is why contempt for Christianity and the Bible is synonymous with mockery for the West.\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999145529755902, \"rank\": 8.545389296436431e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"why contempt\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bible\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1636}, {\"ngram\": \"mockery\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The current civil war within Western civilization is a war between the Left and the Bible.\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The current civil war\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"Western civilization\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"a war\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"the Left\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bible\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1767}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is also the reason the Los Angeles Dodgers not only allowed a group called \\\"Sisters of Perpetual Indulgence\\\" -- a self-described \\\"order of queer and trans nuns\\\" that mimics and mocks Catholic nuns -- to perform prior to a Dodgers game.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1796, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Dodgers\", \"score\": 0.9937151563161023, \"rank\": 0.006253856417171485, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Dodgers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Dodgers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Dodgers\"}, {\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 0.9999996513384456, \"rank\": 2.016379967676249e-07, \"text\": \"trans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}, {\"begin\": 1956, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999731699, \"rank\": 2.6458696529048782e-11, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1995, \"end\": 2002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Dodgers\", \"score\": 0.9922949458203099, \"rank\": 0.006754478900988747, \"text\": \"Dodgers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc